2014,
<span style=3D"color:#1F497D"><a href=3D"http://www.cbpp.org/research/ryan-=
plan-gets-69-percent-of-its-budget-cuts-from-programs-for-people-with-low-o=
r-moderate">fully 69 percent of cuts</a>
</span>($3.3 trillion out of $4.8 trillion) are to programs for low-income =
people like Medicaid, Pell Grants, SNAP/food stamps, and the like.<o:p></o:=
